However, during the late Meiji period, railway construction destroyed the front section. Additionally, the rear section was heavily damaged during World War II due to the establishment of an army anti-aircraft gun command post. Cylindrical {{ill|haniwa|ja|埴輪|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/haniwa|qq=}} fragments recovered from the tumulus suggest its construction dates back to the mid-{{ill|5th century|ja|5世紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/5th century|qq=}}.

