== Overview ==

The kofun is located on a sand dune 1.8 kilometers north of the {{ill|Gion‐Nagasuka Kofun Group|lt=Gion‐Nagasuka Kofun Group|lt=Gion-Nagasuka Kofun Cluster|ja|祇園・長須賀古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gion-Nagasuka Kofun Cluster|qq=}}, which includes late-period chief kofun such as {{ill|Kinreizuka Kofun|lt=Kinreizuka Kofun|lt=Kane no Suzu Kofun|ja|金鈴塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kane no Suzu Kofun|qq=}}. Its main axis aligns northeast-southwest, and it was originally over 110 meters long, making it the third-largest kofun in Chiba Prefecture.<ref name=Chiba/> 

